test_prompts.prompt:
Find the bug in this Python function and explain a minimal fix:

def factorial(n):
    if n == 0:
        return 0
    return n * factorial(n - 1)

Find the undefined behavior in this C++ code and explain a minimal fix:

std::vector<int> values{1, 2, 3};
for (std::size_t i = 0; i <= values.size(); ++i) {
    std::cout << values[i] << '\n';
}

This function should return the sum of the first n natural numbers (1..n) but returns the wrong total. Find the bug and explain a minimal fix:

def sum_to_n(n):
    total = 0
    for i in range(n):
        total += i
    return total

This JavaScript function should return an array of fetched results but resolves before the work finishes. Find the bug and explain a minimal fix:

async function loadAll(ids) {
  const results = [];
  ids.forEach(async (id) => {
    const r = await fetch(`/item/${id}`);
    results.push(await r.json());
  });
  return results;
}

